{{merge|History of the Constitution of Chile|date=June 2018}}
{{more footnotes|date=December 2012}}
{{Politics of Chile}}
The current '''Political Constitution of the Republic of Chile''', approved by [[Chile]]an voters in a controversial [[Chilean constitutional referendum, 1980|plebiscite]] on September 11, 1980, under the military dictatorship of [[Augusto Pinochet]], partially effective March 11, 1981, fully effective 11 March 1990 and amended considerably on August 17, 1989 (via [[Chilean political reform referendum, 1989|referendum]]) and on September 22, 2005 (legislatively), and also in 1991, 1994, 1997, 1999, 2000, 2001, 2003, 2007, 2008, 2009 and 2010, replaced the earlier [[Chilean Constitution of 1925|constitution of 1925]]. It is Chile's eighth constitution.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chronology|url=https://www.constituteproject.org/ontology/chronology?lang=en|website=Constitute|accessdate=22 April 2015}}</ref>

[[Image:Constitución Política de la República de Chile 1980.jpg|thumb|upright|Political Constitution of the Republic of Chile of 1980]]

==Legitimacy==
{{expand section|date=January 2015}}
According to law professor, Camel Cazor Aliste, the Constitution of 1980 has problems of legitimacy stemming from two facts. First, the writing commission was not representative of the [[political spectrum]] of Chile. Its members were hand-picked by the [[Military dictatorship of Chile (1973–90)|dictatorship of Pinochet]] and deliberately excluded opponents of the regime. Secondly, the constitution "approval" was achieved through the controversial and tightly government-controlled referendum of 1980.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Cazor Aliste |first=Camel |date=2000 |title=Democracia y constitucion en Chile |url=http://mingaonline.uach.cl/scielo.php?pid=S0718-09502000000100003&script=sci_arttext |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518062933/http://mingaonline.uach.cl/scielo.php?pid=S0718-09502000000100003&script=sci_arttext |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2015-05-18 |journal=[[Revista de Derecho]] |publisher=[[Austral University of Chile]] |volume=IX |issue= |pages=25–34 |doi= |access-date=30 April 2015 }}</ref>

==Timeline of Constitutions==
* ''Reglamento para el arreglo de la Autoridad Ejecutiva Provisoria de Chile 1811''
* ''Reglamento Constitucional 1812''
* ''Reglamento para el gobierno Provisorio 1814''
* ''Constitución de 1818''
* ''Constitución de 1822''
* ''Constitución de 1823''
* ''Ensayo Federal de 1826''
* ''Constitución de 1828''
* ''[[Chilean Constitution of 1833|Constitución de 1833]]'' - Written among others by [[Mariano Egaña]] and [[Manuel José Gandarillas]]
** Reinterpreted after the [[1891 Chilean Civil War]] augmenting the power of the [[National Congress of Chile]]
* ''[[Chilean Constitution of 1925|Constitución de 1925]]'' - Written among others by [[Arturo Alessandri Palma]] and [[José Maza]]
* ''Constitución de 1980'' - Written among others by [[Jaime Guzmán]]
**Has been reformed in 1989, 1991, 1994, 1997, 1999, 2000, 2001, 2003, 2005, 2007, 2008, 2009 and 2010.

